 study of the hit/effect of green revolution technologies in Bangladesh, has written about this interaction clearly. In villages with a majority of rice cropped 
 in high-cooperating with/producing/giving up varieties, he identifies higher farming-based incomes, higher farming-based wages and higher nonfarm income per person compared to villages 
 still dependent on traditional varieties. The higher nonfarm income in rich villages reflects a greater concentration of high-return nonfarm activity 
 (transport and services) and less low-wage company, construction and 
